1. If labels are derived or waiver (default)
2. If the scale is discrete
3. If the breaks have non-null names
4. If the names array has a length greater than 0

If all conditions are true, it sets the labels to the names of the breaks. Otherwise, it falls back to the original behavior of using the scale's labels.

